data.name: Raticate

attacks.name: Sharp Teeth
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 30 more damage; if tails, this attack does 10 damage.

data.flavorText: This Pokémon sometimes hunts for food in rivers, swimming using the small webs between the toes on its rear legs.

attacks.name: Dark Seed
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn. Put 5 damage counters on the Defending Pokémon at the end of your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Spread Poison
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.name: Raticate

attacks.name: Recruit
attacks.text: Look at your opponent's hand, choose a Supporter card you find there, and discard it. Then, use the effect of that card as the effect of this attack.

attacks.name: Extend Fang
attacks.text: If Raticate has a Pokémon Tool card attached to it, this attack does 20 damage plus 40 more damage.

data.flavorText: It whittles its constantly growing fangs by gnawing on hard things. It can chew apart cinder walls.

data.name: Raticate

attacks.name: Razor-Sharp Incisors
attacks.text: Does 10 damage times the number of damage counters on the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Gnaw Up
attacks.text: Discard a Special Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Its whiskers help it to maintain balance. Its fangs never stop growing, so it gnaws to pare them down.

data.name: Raticate

attacks.name: Super Fang
attacks.text: Does damage to the Defending Pokémon equal to half the Defending Pokémon's remaining HP (rounded up to the nearest 10).

data.flavorText: It uses its whiskers to maintain its balance. It seems to slow down if they are cut off.

attacks.text: During your next turn, Lt. Surge's Raticate's Double-edge attack's damage (base damage and damage to itself) is doubled.

data.name: Alolan Raticate

attacks.name: Evil Orders
attacks.text: Search your deck for a number of cards up to the number of your Benched Pokémon and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Endeavor
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

data.flavorText: This gourmet Pokémon is particular about the taste and freshness of its food. Restaurants where Raticate live have a good reputation.

attacks.name: Find
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for a Trainer card or a Supporter card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand.

attacks.name: Enhanced Fang
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool card attached to it, this attack does 50 more damage.

attacks.name: Hyper Fang
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

data.flavorText: It forms a group of Rattata, which it assumes command of. Each group has its own territory, and disputes over food happen often.

data.name: Alolan Raticate-GX
rules: Pokémon-GX rule: When your Pokémon-GX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Chuck Away
attacks.text: Discard up to 2 cards from your hand. This attack does 40 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

attacks.name: Hyper Fang
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Item Maniac-GX
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 6 Item cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

attacks.name: Transfer Junk
attacks.text: Put a Team Plasma Pokémon, a Team Plasma Trainer card, and a Team Plasma Energy card from your discard pile into your hand.

data.flavorText: With its long fangs, this surprisingly violent Pokémon can gnaw away even thick concrete with ease.
